cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - This paper focuses on multi-modal machine translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the cs.CL category. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper also heavily relies on visual information and proposes a co-attention model to capture interactions between visual and textual features, which falls under the cs.CV category. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The proposed approach involves joint training of translation models and regularization techniques, which falls under the cs.LG category. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a novel approach to improve the use of visual information in machine translation, which falls under the cs.AI category. 
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper involves the use of attention mechanisms to retrieve relevant information from the image, which falls under the cs.IR category.
